com.pb.sawdust.util.array

Class TypeSafeArrayFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.util.array.TypeSafeArrayFactory

  • public class TypeSafeArrayFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    The TypeSafeArrayFactory holds static methods which provide TypeSafeArray implementations.

      • typeSafeArray

        public static <T> TypeSafeArray<T> typeSafeArray(java.lang.Class<T> type,
                                 int... dimensions)
        Get a type safe array holding the specified type.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type the returned array holds.
        Parameters:
        type - The class of the type the array will hold.
        dimensions - The dimensionality of the returned array. Each value specifies the size of a dimension in the array, so dimensions.length indicates the number of dimensions in the array.
        Returns:
        a type safe array of size dimensions holding T.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NegativeArraySizeException - if any of values in dimensions are less than zero.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if no dimensions are specified (dimensions.length == 0).

      • typeSafeArray

        public static TypeSafeArray<?> typeSafeArray(JavaType type,
                             int... dimensions)
        Get a type safe array holding the specified type.
        Parameters:
        type - The type the returned array will hold. If type is JavaType.OBJECT, then an Object array will be returned, otherwise the returned array will hold the specified primitive.
        dimensions - The dimensionality of the returned array. Each value specifies the size of a dimension in the array, so dimensions.length indicates the number of dimensions in the array.
        Returns:
        a type safe array of size dimensions holding the type corresponding to types.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NegativeArraySizeException - if any of values in dimensions are less than zero.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if no dimensions are specified (dimensions.length == 0).
